"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-paris-summer-games-daily-viewers-guide-tv-team-usa\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Check out Sports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daily Rings, our daily Olympics podcast from Mitch Goldich and Dan Gartland.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 78, \"end\": 83, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"score\": 0.9999986302309767, \"rank\": 1.3694399291700955e-06, \"text\": \"Mitch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\"}, {\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts (Apple,Spotify) and find clips onSI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s YouTube page.\", \"from\": 110, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 152, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9026105698648912e-13, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most overwhelming sporting event to follow.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike March Madness or the World Cup, there are dozens of different sports, countless rules to familiarize yourself with and the possibility of being fully entranced by an event you can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t quite remember if you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve ever seen before.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This summer in Paris they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll hand out medals in 329 events across 39 sports.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t watch all of them\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094though the brave among us will try\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094so this road map is a solid starting point.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a daily viewing guide to check out some of the top competitors and biggest moments, with a taste of the niche and novel.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes everyone will be talking about and the sports that will give you fun facts to impress your friends.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A plan to make the most of these 19 days that you can never totally plan for.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00932, July 24  As is customary, the Olympics will begin with a fun trip through the negative integers portion of your calendar, as a handful of team sports start play before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s soccer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094featuring under-23 squads with up to three overage players\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094kicks off on Day \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00932, and the U.S. will face the hosts at the famed Marseille Stadium, aka Stade V\\u00c3\\u00a9lodrome.\\u00c2  Day \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00931, July 25  Since being introduced in 2016, rugby sevens has become a Games staple.\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fast-paced, with matches played in frantic seven-minute halves, and it happens over just six competition days, so catch some action while you can.\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Preliminary rounds in archery and handball also begin, as well as group play in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s soccer, with France, ranked No.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9970053104919262, \"rank\": 0.0019600839642876047, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3 in the world, taking on Colombia.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8001433456809027, \"rank\": 0.2497760416022458, \"text\": \"Colombia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USWNT vs. Zambia  The U.S. women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s national team will look much differentthan the squad that captured the bronze in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999707506508, \"rank\": 2.9233223135009157e-08, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That roster had an average age of 30.8, but after the retirement of many pillars, including Carli Lloyd, Julie Ertz, Megan Rapinoe and Sam Mewis, we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see a more youthful group led by a new coach, former Chelsea manager Emma Hayes.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2070130283533674e-82, \"text\": \"Carli Lloyd\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carli_Lloyd\"}, {\"begin\": 2072, \"end\": 2082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Ertz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julie Ertz\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Ertz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julie_Ertz\"}, {\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Megan Rapinoe\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Rapinoe\"}, {\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Mewis\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Mewis\"}, {\"begin\": 2174, \"end\": 2181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\", \"score\": 0.9998657331340476, \"rank\": 0.0001342848958214571, \"text\": \"Chelsea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C._Women\"}, {\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hayes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eager to end a gold medal drought that dates back to London 2012, the team will lean on the leadership of 24-year-old defender Naomi Girma and captain Lindsey Horan.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9055452503460767e-43, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Girma\", \"score\": 0.999998433174687, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Naomi Girma\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Girma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naomi_Girma\"}, {\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindsey Horan\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Horan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up top, a deep forward pool headlined by Mallory Swanson, Sophia Smith and Trinity Rodman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094all playing in their first Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094will be tasked with remedying the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s recent scoring woes.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2410, \"end\": 2417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Mallory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.974423712385029e-15, \"text\": \"Mallory\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Mallory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Mallory\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"score\": 0.9999999989595381, \"rank\": 1.0385756088648561e-09, \"text\": \"Swanson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swanson\"}, {\"begin\": 2427, \"end\": 2433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4295559987409822e-13, \"text\": \"Sophia\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Peletier\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity\", \"score\": 0.9774114018919584, \"rank\": 0.023110591113916057, \"text\": \"Trinity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Clare Brennan  Day 0, July 26  The official start of these Olympics will be one of a kind.\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than walking around a stadium, athlete delegations will parade through the heart of Paris in boats along the winding Seine.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2748, \"end\": 2753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2781, \"end\": 2786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.041684605075159e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony will still feature colorful team outfits, the waving of flags and traditional fanfare, such as the cauldron lighting, all in front of more than 200,000 fans.\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Peyton Manning and Kelly Clarkson will join Mike Tirico in the NBC booth to regale viewers with facts about faraway nations.\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peyton Manning\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\"}, {\"begin\": 2986, \"end\": 3000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}, {\"begin\": 3011, \"end\": 3022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mike Tirico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\"}, {\"begin\": 3030, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.7067785591281792, \"rank\": 0.41487031133705987, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 1, July 27  Turn your early attention to the pool, where the Games start off with a bang thanks to a battle of legends in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 400-meter freestyle event.\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ariarne Titmus will once again go head-to-head with the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Katie Ledecky.\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3274, \"end\": 3288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus won this race at the Tokyo Games and at  the 2023 world championships last July, where she set a world record.The 27-year-old Ledecky will be all over the pool deck and your screensduring the first week, as she looks to add to her seven gold and 10 total Olympic medals.\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3354, \"end\": 3360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first competition in primetime features another pair of signature swimming events: the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4X100-meter freestyle relays.\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus: Day 1 will also see medals handed out in seven other sports: diving, fencing, judo, rugby sevens, shooting, skateboarding and the cycling road race.\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 2, July 28  You might think fencing isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t your forte, but give it a try on the second day of action, which includes medal bouts for men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s \\u00c3\\u00a9p\\u00c3\\u00a9e and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s foil, where the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lee Kiefer will attempt to defend her Tokyo gold.\", \"from\": 3933, \"to\": 4174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4125, \"end\": 4135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lee Kiefer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\"}, {\"begin\": 4163, \"end\": 4168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sabre, Olympic newcomer Colin Heathcock is a frontrunner.\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4220, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Partridge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0511557379169255e-28, \"text\": \"Heathcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Partridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Partridge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 18-year-old previously competed for Germany before joining Team USA.\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4288, \"end\": 4295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999360752574, \"rank\": 6.392474874660526e-08, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4311, \"end\": 4319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.540752841176376e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:Badminton?\", \"from\": 4322, \"to\": 4338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball?\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indoor volleyball?\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Table tennis?\", \"from\": 4376, \"to\": 4389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your pick of sports with nets.\", \"from\": 4390, \"to\": 4425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Eiffel Tower Stadium, the U.S. women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s beach volleyball pair of Kelly Cheng and Sara Hughes enter as top medal contenders after their 2023 world title.\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4499, \"end\": 4504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.737618122727006e-20, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 4520, \"end\": 4526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8206116104466563e-13, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 3, July 29  Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s water polo squad is a dynasty, having won three straight Olympic golds plus a slew of world championships over that time span.\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Captain Maggie Steffens set the Olympic career goal-scoring record in Tokyo and is back for more.\", \"from\": 4754, \"to\": 4851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4762, \"end\": 4777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maggie Steffens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maggie_Steffens\"}, {\"begin\": 4824, \"end\": 4829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second game in three days will be a rematch of the Tokyo gold medal match against Spain, and the U.S will have the financial backing of a new sponsor: 65-year-old rapper Flavor Flav, who stepped in to help the team after seeing Steffens\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s call for support in an Instagram post.\", \"from\": 4852, \"to\": 5144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4916, \"end\": 4921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"t