ball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999890861, \"rank\": 1.0049661668684109e-11, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:Canoe and kayak slalom are entertaining to watch, as athletes contend with man-made whitewater rapids and maneuver their boats around buoys.\", \"from\": 5314, \"to\": 5460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5330, \"end\": 5335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"score\": 0.5967115223073663, \"rank\": 0.6758516680455334, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayaking\"}, {\"begin\": 5336, \"end\": 5342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\", \"score\": 0.5871612749640197, \"rank\": 0.7031095929513229, \"text\": \"slalom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canoe_slalom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, the kayak cross event\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094which features four kayakers on the course simultaneously\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094will make its Olympic debut a few days later.\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5464, \"end\": 5469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Evy Leibfarth, 20, is set to compete in all three events.\", \"from\": 5601, \"to\": 5671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5614, \"end\": 5627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evy_Leibfarth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evy Leibfarth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evy_Leibfarth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evy_Leibfarth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 4, July 30  The stage is set for the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gymnastics team final.\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094which has medaled in seven straight Games, with golds in 1996, 2012 and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009916\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094isheadlined by Simone Biles, 27, who returns to the Olympic stage after Tokyo, where she battled the twisties but still earned a silver (in the team event) and a bronze (in balance beam).\", \"from\": 5747, \"to\": 6025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5853, \"end\": 5865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 5910, \"end\": 5915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:If you think those table tennis games in your basement are intense, check out the mixed doubles medal matches\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll put your game to shame.\", \"from\": 6027, \"to\": 6178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 5, July 31  Looking to watch athletes compete in three different sports and finish in a single day?\", \"from\": 6180, \"to\": 6283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We humbly suggest the triathlon.\", \"from\": 6284, \"to\": 6316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 50 competitors are slated to swim 1,500 meters in the Seine, cycle 40 kilometers, riding along the Champs-\\u00c3\\u0089lys\\u00c3\\u00a9es, and run 10 kilometers through the heart of Paris.\", \"from\": 6317, \"to\": 6493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6381, \"end\": 6386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.041684605075159e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 6487, \"end\": 6492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s event, contested over the same course, will take place the day after the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s.\", \"from\": 6494, \"to\": 6589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing  Although France has plenty of beaches, the surfing competition will take place on the other side of the globe, at the iconic Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o, located in the crystal blue South Pacific waters off the coast of Tahiti in French Polynesia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a 9,800-mile trek from the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 6591, \"to\": 6876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6609, \"end\": 6615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9970053104919262, \"rank\": 0.0019600839642876047, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6804, \"end\": 6810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.120516690754527e-17, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 6814, \"end\": 6820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999812078332491, \"rank\": 1.8758394179850397e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6860, \"end\": 6875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3739147613281575e-42, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 5 is the scheduled medal day, but there is a 10-day window built in so organizers can plan around optimal weather and wave conditions.\", \"from\": 6877, \"to\": 7015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. stars who competed in the sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s debut in Tokyo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094gold medal winner Carissa Moore,2023 World Surf League champ Caroline Marksand Hawai\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099i native John John Florence\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094all return.\", \"from\": 7016, \"to\": 7206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other headliners in the field of 48 include 14-year-old Siqi Yang, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first Olympic surfer; Brazil\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Filipe Toledo, the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009923 WSL title winner; and France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Johanne Defay, the only European woman currently competing on the pro tour.\", \"from\": 7207, \"to\": 7450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7317, \"end\": 7330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filipe Toledo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipe_Toledo\"}, {\"begin\": 7375, \"end\": 7388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johanne_Defay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Johanne Defay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johanne_Defay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johanne_Defay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 6, Aug. 1  The U.S. looks to keep its streak alive in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all-around individual gymnastics final, where it has won five straight golds: Carly Patterson (Athens), Nastia Liukin (Beijing), Gabby Douglas (London), Biles (Rio) and Suni Lee (Tokyo).\", \"from\": 7452, \"to\": 7710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7602, \"end\": 7617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carly_Patterson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carly Patterson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carly_Patterson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carly_Patterson\"}, {\"begin\": 7619, \"end\": 7625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9007258013493605e-46, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7628, \"end\": 7641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nastia_Liukin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nastia Liukin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nastia_Liukin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nastia_Liukin\"}, {\"begin\": 7643, \"end\": 7650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7707172962667335e-42, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7653, \"end\": 7666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabby Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\"}, {\"begin\": 7668, \"end\": 7674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999508873, \"rank\": 4.849851122368269e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 7693, \"end\": 7701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 7703, \"end\": 7708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 7, Aug. 2  Trampoline gymnastics is a one-day event, so clear your Friday plans if you don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t want to miss it.\", \"from\": 7712, \"to\": 7827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men and women will perform mesmerizing routines that consist of 10 skills\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094all sorts of flips, twists and somersaults\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094while bouncing 25 feet in the air.\", \"from\": 7828, \"to\": 7983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Zhu Xueying looks to defend her gold, while Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Bryony Page is a two-time medalist.\", \"from\": 7984, \"to\": 8091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8056, \"end\": 8067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryony Page\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:The finals for men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s BMX racing feature a pack of eight riders speeding over jumps and around steep, high-banking turns.\", \"from\": 8093, \"to\": 8235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 8, Aug. 3  Tennis will be a spectacle throughout the Olympics, with the event taking place on the famed clay at Roland Garros, home of the French Open.\", \"from\": 8237, \"to\": 8392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8353, \"end\": 8366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.536508403795139e-13, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That will add a unique twist to the event, akin to when the London Olympics played on the grass at Wimbledon.\", \"from\": 8393, \"to\": 8502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8453, \"end\": 8468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.493756020368194e-49, \"text\": \"London Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While play begins on the first day of the Games, Saturday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s slate features the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles gold medal match, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doubles gold and the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles bronze.\", \"from\": 8503, \"to\": 8676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After welcoming her first child in April, Tokyo gold medalist Belinda Bencic of Switzerland won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t defend in Paris, but Poland\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Iga \\u00c5\\u009awi\\u00c4\\u0085tek, the current world No.\", \"from\": 8677, \"to\": 8845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8757, \"end\": 8768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.873380618123904, \"rank\": 0.14497617558674064, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 8787, \"end\": 8792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 8809, \"end\": 8812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.089122100454949e-33, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1, and the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Coco Gauff have qualified.\", \"from\": 8846, \"to\": 8892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8866, \"end\": 8876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus: The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s eight rowing finals have a rich Olympic history, as seen in the 2023 movieThe Boys in the Boat.\", \"from\": 8894, \"to\": 9022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 9, Aug. 4  Organizers added an extra day at the pool to the schedule for Paris, which means there are now two competition days featuring the Big Three sports, namely swimming, track and field and gymnastics.\", \"from\": 9024, \"to\": 9235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9101, \"end\": 9106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is the second day of an Olympics version of the sports equinox, and it happens to feature the fan-favorite men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100-meter final.American Noah Lyleswon gold at the 2023 world championships.\", \"from\": 9236, \"to\": 9432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9381, \"end\": 9385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"score\": 0.7414847550607274, \"rank\": 0.34863049101708604, \"text\": \"Noah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:The final round of the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s golf tournament will be played,featuring top names like 2024 Masters champ Scottie Scheffler.\", \"from\": 9434, \"to\": 9564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9546, \"end\": 9563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 10, Aug. 5  It may surprise you to learn that field hockey is one of the oldest Olympic team sports, dating back to 1908 for men (1980 for women).\", \"from\": 9566, \"to\": 9716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was not part of the program at Paris 1924, but has been included in every Games since.\", \"from\": 9717, \"to\": 9806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 10 features the four women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s quarterfinals matches.\", \"from\": 9807, \"to\": 9864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After missing the cut in Tokyo, the U.S. women qualified for Paris with a roster that featured 16 Pennsylvania natives\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094each of whom would be making their Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 9865, \"to\": 10035, \"entities\": 