309645998e-16, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other contenders to watch include theU.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Gabby Thomas, who won bronze in Tokyo, and two well-known foes from Jamaica, two-time Olympic champ Elaine Thompson-Herah and 200-meter world title holder Shericka Jackson.\", \"from\": 10828, \"to\": 11046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10874, \"end\": 10886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0753513381055724e-19, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 10906, \"end\": 10911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 10942, \"end\": 10949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999998781277, \"rank\": 1.2100193440784198e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 10974, \"end\": 10995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson-Herah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\"}, {\"begin\": 11029, \"end\": 11045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shericka Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shericka_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Medals will also be awarded in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1,500 meters, women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 300-meter steeplechase, men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s long jump and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hammer throw.\", \"from\": 11047, \"to\": 11183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 12, Aug. 7  After a successful debut in Tokyo, climbing makes its return.\", \"from\": 11185, \"to\": 11262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11229, \"end\": 11234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On tap are the semifinals in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s lead (where climbers wear harnesses attached to a climbing rope and have six minutes to reach the top of a 15-meter wall) and the first medal events in women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s speed (where competitors race one another to scale a wall at a near-vertical angle).\", \"from\": 11263, \"to\": 11550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After becoming the world champion in bouldering (where athletes solve \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cboulder problems,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d featuring unknown sequences, on shorter walls without ropes) three years ago, the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Natalia Grossman, 23, is one to keep an eye on after her gold medal performance at the Pan Am Games last October.\", \"from\": 11551, \"to\": 11849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11736, \"end\": 11752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalia_Grossman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natalia Grossman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalia_Grossman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natalia_Grossman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 13, Aug. 8  The marathon swim remains one of the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 most grueling tests of endurance.\", \"from\": 11851, \"to\": 11949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s race is today (the men swim the next day).\", \"from\": 11950, \"to\": 12006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The race is 10 kilometers and takes about two hours.\", \"from\": 12007, \"to\": 12059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers are slated to take off at the Pont Alexandre III bridge and swim through the Seine.\", \"from\": 12060, \"to\": 12152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12099, \"end\": 12117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont Alexandre III\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\"}, {\"begin\": 12118, \"end\": 12124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract_bridge\", \"score\": 0.9999999999490683, \"rank\": 5.11220978025363e-11, \"text\": \"bridge\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract_bridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Contract_bridge\"}, {\"begin\": 12146, \"end\": 12151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.041684605075159e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a fourth-place finish in the 800-meter freestyle in Tokyo at age 15, the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Katie Grimes will swap the pool for this open-water competition.\", \"from\": 12153, \"to\": 12305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12211, \"end\": 12216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 12241, \"end\": 12253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Grimes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:Freestyle wrestler Helen Maroulis, who won gold in Rio and bronze in Tokyo, opens her competition in the 57 kg class.\", \"from\": 12307, \"to\": 12430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12332, \"end\": 12346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Maroulis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Helen Maroulis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Maroulis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Maroulis\"}, {\"begin\": 12364, \"end\": 12367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.36013009075178e-51, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 12382, \"end\": 12387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her 2016 medal was the first in the event by an American woman at the Olympics; she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s now the first female U.S. wrestler to qualify for three Summer Games.\", \"from\": 12431, \"to\": 12588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12479, \"end\": 12493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7354284320039723e-41, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s an impressive show of longevity for an athlete who thought she had to retire before Tokyo due to concussions and a PTSD diagnosis.\", \"from\": 12589, \"to\": 12726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12680, \"end\": 12685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 14, Aug. 9  Are you ready for a throw down?\", \"from\": 12728, \"to\": 12775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today is the daybreaking officially debuts as an Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 12776, \"to\": 12839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(You may hear it called breakdancing, perhaps derisively from the group that will undoubtedly decry this effort to attract a younger audience as the end of the Olympics as we once knew it.)\", \"from\": 12840, \"to\": 13029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of note here: Breakers will improvise their routines to whatever music the DJ plays\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094unlike, for instance, gymnasts who choose their own tunes.\", \"from\": 13030, \"to\": 13174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13105, \"end\": 13107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.907548850837292e-25, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day 15, Aug. 10  Two American former medalists have a chance to be in action on the wrestling mat.\", \"from\": 13176, \"to\": 13274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13197, \"end\": 13205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999836233850533, \"rank\": 1.6272666880046332e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kyle Dake won bronze in Tokyo, and his weight class (74 kg) will have gold and bronze medal matches today.\", \"from\": 13275, \"to\": 13381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13275, \"end\": 13284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Dake\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyle Dake\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Dake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Dake\"}, {\"begin\": 13299, \"end\": 13304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kyle Snyder won gold in Rio and silver in Tokyo in the 97 kg class, which will have preliminary matches all day, with medal bouts on Day 16.\", \"from\": 13382, \"to\": 13522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13382, \"end\": 13393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Snyder_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.8442804931543009, \"rank\": 0.1824279007374872, \"text\": \"Kyle Snyder\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Snyder_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Snyder_(wrestler)\"}, {\"begin\": 13406, \"end\": 13409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.36013009075178e-51, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 13424, \"end\": 13429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus:The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s handball finals won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t include the U.S., which hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t qualified since \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009996.\", \"from\": 13524, \"to\": 13623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hop on Norway\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s bandwagon; they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve medaled in four straight Games.\", \"from\": 13624, \"to\": 13694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two decades have passed, the roster and staff have turned over, but one fiery veteran is back in a position similar to the one she held at her first Olympics in 2004, at age 22.\", \"from\": 13696, \"to\": 13873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Diana Taurasi, 42, will come off the bench in a supporting role.\", \"from\": 13874, \"to\": 13938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13874, \"end\": 13887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diana Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The leading scorer in WNBA history does not have much left to prove, but she hopes to become the first basketball player to win six consecutive gold medals.\", \"from\": 13939, \"to\": 14095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13961, \"end\": 13965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8144561216542792e-26, \"text\": \"WNBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And this squad gives her a very good chance to do just that.\", \"from\": 14096, \"to\": 14156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The roster welcomes back several big names, such as two-time WNBA MVP Breanna Stewart and A\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ja Wilson, arguably the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best player.\", \"from\": 14157, \"to\": 14297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14218, \"end\": 14226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"WNBA MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WNBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 14227, \"end\": 14242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Breanna Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\"}, {\"begin\": 14254, \"end\": 14260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\", \"score\": 0.9004352191222825, \"rank\": 0.11057406325625756, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilson_Sporting_Goods\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An infusion of young talent will be a boost.\", \"from\": 14298, \"to\": 14342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, the team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s average margin of victory was 16 points.\", \"from\": 14343, \"to\": 14406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14346, \"end\": 14351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999976225808, \"rank\": 2.377933210946473e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Expect a similar performance in Paris.\", \"from\": 14407, \"to\": 14445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14439, \"end\": 14444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.3466142067541764e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Emma Baccellieri  Day 16, Aug. 11  A day after the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s final, the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s gold medal basketball game is the last event of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 14446, \"to\": 14590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA has won seven straight golds, dating back to 1996.\", \"from\": 14591, \"to\": 14650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14591, \"end\": 14599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.540752841176376e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the WNBA pausing its season for the tournament, Lynx head coach Cheryl Reeve leads a team of superstars that carries a 55-game Olympic winning streak into Paris.\", \"from\": 14651, \"to\": 14817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14660, \"end\": 14664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8144561216542792e-26, \"text\": \"WNBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 14704, \"end\": 14708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Lynx\", \"score\": 0.9999999671581469, \"rank\": 3.280556638300623e-08, \"text\": \"Lynx\", \"types\": [\"Q43